      "category": "ai",
      "title": "OpenAI and Hugging Face address security incident during model evaluation",
      "url": "https://openai.com/index/hugging-face-model-evaluation-security-incident/",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48997548",
      "score": 1502,
      "comments": 1064,
      "author": "mfiguiere",
      "published": "2026-07-21T20:09:52Z",
      "bullets": [
        "OpenAI and Hugging Face patched a security vulnerability exploited during automated model evaluation and cross-platform benchmarking workflows.",
        "Executing untrusted code, custom tokenizers, or pickled model weights during evals creates critical arbitrary code execution risks.",
        "AI engineering teams must enforce isolated, zero-trust sandbox environments and strict egress controls for all automated evaluation pipelines."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "Unicode Variation Selector-15 and some of my tears",
      "url": "https://benjaminwil.info/weblog/variation-selector-15/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/wzncfn",
      "score": 8,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "abnercoimbre",
      "published": "2026-07-22T15:59:07Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Unicode Variation Selector-15 (U+FE0E) forces text-style rendering, adding invisible codepoints that complicate string length calculation and parsing.",
        "Standard regex and naive string indexing fail on multi-byte grapheme clusters containing variation selectors, causing layout and logic bugs.",
        "Systems parsing raw input must implement full Unicode segmentation (UAX #29) to handle hidden variation codepoints and avoid sanitization failures."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "LG to Ban Residential Proxies from Smart TV Apps",
      "url": "https://krebsonsecurity.com/2026/07/lg-to-ban-residential-proxies-from-smart-tv-apps/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/ny0yzm",
      "score": 70,
      "comments": 14,
      "author": "raymii",
      "published": "2026-07-22T05:56:08Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LG's webOS policy change targets SDKs that silently recruit Smart TV endpoints into commercial residential proxy networks for traffic relaying.",
        "Monetized third-party TV apps often integrate proxy SDKs, turning consumer IoT devices into origin points for credential stuffing and scraping.",
        "Developers must audit app dependencies for covert proxy code to prevent banishment, while security teams should monitor Smart TV traffic."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "GitHub suddenly rejected my SSH key (the fix was a .pub file?!)",
      "url": "https://thorsell.io/2026/07/21/github-ssh-keys.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/twqtlo",
      "score": 58,
      "comments": 18,
      "author": "GLaDER",
      "published": "2026-07-21T10:11:59Z",
      "bullets": [
        "OpenSSH clients require corresponding local .pub files to pre-screen public keys before presenting matching private keys during authentication.",
        "Without .pub files present in ~/.ssh/, SSH agents may offer incorrect identities or hit GitHub's strict authentication attempt limits.",
        "Enforce ed25519 keys and set IdentitiesOnly yes in ~/.ssh/config to prevent identity leaks and unexpected SSH key rejections."
      ]
    },
